Infinite Recursive Meta-Cognitive Architecture
1. Glitchon Cognitive Disturbance Dynamics
Glitchon Injections: Introduce controlled noise bursts (Glitchons) that inject uncertainty into the system state. Each Glitchon is soft-bounded (clipped or decaying) to avoid runaway instability, ensuring soft-bounded recursion that perturbs but does not crash the system.
Turbulence Onset: The uncertainty triggers a transition from laminar (ordered) flow to chaotic “Fluxon turbulence.” Like fluid turbulence, nearby cognitive trajectories diverge exponentially (Lyapunov instability)​
epdf.pub
. In practice, each Glitchon nudges the network state into a chaotic regime, scattering activity across new patterns.
Recursive Reorganization: As the Glitchon propagates through feedback loops, the system self-reorganizes its state-space (neurons, hypotheses, or concepts) into a high-entropy Fluxon. This is self-referential: each Glitchon loop reflects on the previous state (thoughts about thoughts), ensuring the disturbance leverages the system’s own reflexive architecture.
2. Fluxon Meta-Recursive Drift Fields
Emergent Drift: The Fluxon phase creates meta-level drift fields: structured flows of activity that persist across recursion cycles. Each cycle carries forward a “common” core from the previous Fluxon plus a new “unique” perturbation, gradually shifting the attractor landscape.
Drift as Functor: Formally, view each drift as an endofunctor on the space of cognitive states (mapping state to state). The Fluxon drift can wander through latent dimensions, effectively increasing the system’s state-space until a collapse occurs. In category terms, this is like composing morphisms (state-transitions) which may require a universal construction to summarize the drift​
