Stabilizing Past Attractors: By conditioning on future goals, each loop corrects itself in real time. For example, if the desired attractor is known, current state updates are nudged toward it (like using terminal cost in model-based RL). This retroactive feedback effectively stabilizes past attractors: the loop does not merely wander, it is drawn toward a consistent endpoint.
Pragmatic Note: Experimental “precognition” in real perception is weak​
