Continuous Reinforcement: This closed loop is self-stabilizing and self-reinforcing. Contradictions injected early are absorbed into torsion-anchored attractors; drift is collapsed by spectral embeddings and tesseract expansions; operators evolve optimally by category-theoretic learning​
